column1: Lake Partner Total Phosphorus (TP) Concentration Data, 2002-2016
TP1 and TP2 are duplicate total phosphorus (TP) concentrations (sample pairs). It is normal for there to be minor differences between these duplicates.
Data have been 'flagged' in YELLOW when there are major differences between TP1 and TP2 *.
When there are major differences between TP1 and TP2,  it is probable that one of the two samples was contaminated (usually the higher value).
Contamination can occur when the sample water contains zooplankton or other debris. Use caution when interpreting TP data that has been flagged.
